core/llm — LLM Client Module
=============================

Unified LLM client layer for the galaxy-selfevolve pipeline.
All agent-side and tool-side model calls route through this module.


## Architecture

### Inheritance hierarchy

```
BaseLLMClient (ABC)  ← base.py
└── OpenAISDKClient  ← base.py  (SDK bootstrap; Chat Completions helpers; shared extraction)
    ├── OpenAIClient             ← openai_client.py      (Responses API)
    │   └── GPTSub2APIClient     ← gpt_sub2api_client.py (haoxiang.ai gateway)
    └── OpenRouterNewAPIClient   ← openrouter_newapi_client.py  (Chat Completions)
        └── OpenRouterTestClient ← openrouter_test_client.py    (cheap smoke-test preset)
```

### Wire API split

| Branch | API route | SDK call | Reasoning summaries |
|--------|-----------|----------|---------------------|
| `OpenAIClient` | Responses API | `client.responses.create()` | Yes — `output[].type="reasoning"` items |
| `OpenRouterNewAPIClient` | Chat Completions | `client.chat.completions.create()` | Best-effort from `message.reasoning_summary` |

Use **Responses API** (OpenAIClient branch) when the gateway exposes it and
reasoning summaries are required. Use **Chat Completions** for OpenRouter and
apihy.com, which do not expose the Responses API route.


## Files

```
base.py                  BaseLLMClient, OpenAISDKClient, LLMResponse, registry
env_utils.py             load_env(), resolve_client_setting() — shared .env helpers
openai_client.py         OpenAIClient  (Responses API, tool calling, web search)
gpt_sub2api_client.py    GPTSub2APIClient  (haoxiang.ai Responses API + secondary key fallback)
openrouter_newapi_client.py  OpenRouterNewAPIClient  (Chat Completions; OpenRouter / apihy.com)
openrouter_test_client.py    OpenRouterTestClient  (cheap preset for manual smoke tests)
tool_client_factory.py   Route-aware factory for tool-side LLM calls
list_models.py           CLI: list available models from any OpenAI-compatible endpoint
__init__.py              Public exports
```


## Client registry

Clients are registered by name via `@register_llm_client("name")`:

| Registry name     | Class                    | Wire API          |
|-------------------|--------------------------|-------------------|
| `openai`          | OpenAIClient             | Responses API     |
| `gpt_sub2api`     | GPTSub2APIClient         | Responses API     |
| `openrouter_newapi` | OpenRouterNewAPIClient | Chat Completions  |
| `openrouter_test` | OpenRouterTestClient     | Chat Completions  |

Resolve by name with `get_llm_client_class(name)` or instantiate directly with
`instantiate_llm_client(name, kwargs)`.


## Credential resolution

Each client reads credentials from environment variables (via `.env`).
Priority: explicit constructor arg → `*_env` kwarg → module-level defaults.

Key env vars:

| Client | API key env | Base URL env |
|--------|-------------|--------------|
| GPTSub2APIClient | `GPT_sub2api_apikey` | `GPT_sub2api_URL` |
| GPTSub2APIClient (fallback) | `GPT_sub2api_apikey_2` | same |
| OpenRouterNewAPIClient | `apihy_API_KEY_qwen` / `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | `apihy_BASE_URL` / `OPENROUTER_BASE_URL` |
| OpenAIClient | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | `OPENAI_BASE_URL` |

`env_utils.resolve_client_setting()` is the shared primitive for this pattern.


## Tool-side routing

`tool_client_factory.py` owns the mapping from tool workflow names ("routes")
to concrete clients and models. Call sites use route names, not client names:

```python
from core.llm.tool_client_factory import build_tool_llm_client

client = build_tool_llm_client(route_name="search_summary")
client = build_tool_llm_client(route_name="read_image")
```

Defined routes: `search_summary`, `webpage_summary`, `llm_inference`,
`ranking_extractor`, `read_image`.

Routes can be overridden at runtime via:
- `config/agent/llm/*.yaml` (Hydra config, takes highest priority)
- `TOOL_TEXT_LLM_CLIENT` / `TOOL_TEXT_MODEL` env vars
- `TOOL_VISION_LLM_CLIENT` / `TOOL_VISION_MODEL` env vars


## LLM YAML configs

`config/agent/llm/*.yaml` — one file per named LLM profile, loaded by Hydra.
Each file specifies `client`, `model`, `max_tokens`, `reasoning_effort`, and
credential env var names. These are the profiles referenced in agent configs
via `llm: gpt_sub2api` etc.


## Reasoning summaries

Reasoning summaries require the Responses API (OpenAIClient branch) with
`reasoning_effort` set. The model decides when to reason based on question
complexity — simple inputs produce `reasoning_tokens=0` and no summary even
with effort set. When the model does reason, `LLMResponse.reasoning_summary`
contains the extracted summary texts.

`ASSISTANT_MESSAGE_EXTRA_FIELDS` (base.py) lists fields agents attach to
assistant message dicts that Chat Completions APIs will reject. Both the agent
layer (writer) and Chat Completions clients (stripper) reference this constant.


## list_models.py

CLI for discovering available model names at any endpoint:

    python -m core.llm.list_models [--api-key-env ENV] [--base-url-env ENV]

Without flags, resolves credentials from the first populated profile in
`DEFAULT_CREDENTIAL_PROFILES`. Override with `LIST_MODELS_API_KEY_ENV` /
`LIST_MODELS_BASE_URL_ENV` env vars.
